        <abstract> 
<p>Recommends publication of Leonard Horner’s account of researches in alluvial deposits of Egypt [<hi rend="italic">Philos. Trans. R. Soc. Lond.</hi> 145 (1855): 105–38]. It contains valuable observations which will probably become of still higher value in future.</p> 
